I usually go through kemco games and this one's only flaw is the character development. The lead is too one dimensional and unlikable, lack of personality besides being revenge driven. Controlling the mob spawn rates has never been done before, a nice touch if you want to raise or lower encounters. Crafting system is linear, it gets to the point that basic attacks and auto battle is enough for non boss fights. Learning more skills for the element you have needs more explanation, I never knew.
it was fun enjoyable to play like the story line
Same as other kenco games, which I like but 8.99 really!
Its a good game but the walking around the dungeon and town are way too......slow

I finished it! Damn, must say this game is quite enjoyable with an interesting plot. The art of the characters are gorgeous and they have interesting personalities as well. There are so many quests and area to increase your level. In short, I love this game so much! Looking forward to play another Kemco game or maybe a sequel of this game. Love you Kemco!

Another great Classic RPG Published by KEMCO! At first, you will doubt the content of every scenario taking place by being a dumb fool for revenge growing to a rational loved person he can be. Together with many obstacles along the way. The unique trait of this game is that you can earn passive skills by quest you completed whether Main, Sub or Guild Quests and can be leveled up. The only fun fact for me in this game is that there are rare items like giving 50 stats to two random current stats‚Äìcan only be acquired in Cash Shop‚Äìbut this game even in Guild Exchange doesn't give that option to be exchanged so you really need hard grinding to finish it. Anyways, there is a feature here called cauldron if your familiar with it-its a nice way to RNG Rare items without Prismic Fruits(In Game Cash Currency). Also, the rebound system is applicable in this game, so spam those skills. There's a Limit Break kind of skill as well, but just play the game already and enough reading this message. Hohoho.

It's a great game. I love the story and combat, but I miss being able to explore an open-world rather than warp to different places. This one I understand because it's a tower; however, like in wizards of brandel, the warping wasn't really needed as much. I mean either way I'm going to play the games, but I still miss open world exploration

A fairly traditional jrpg. There are some typos, but it doesn't really distract from the games message. To this point the main character is really one dimensional and it's a bit sad we aren't seeing the beginnings of character development. Mechanics are what you'd expect from a turned based jrpg. That being said I've spent about 5 hours on the game on one sitting so the gameplay outside the story is enjoyable.
Very relaxing game o play,great controls and game play but not as good as the older rpgs please bring them back

If you've played any Kemco/ExeCreate games before, you'll be in very familiar territory. There's lots to do. No gacha is required to finish the game. I do think they should bring back free premium currency. With the price hike to $8.99 from $4.99 for these games, I take full advantage of the refund period, and if I'm not loving a game, well, back it goes. This is the first one I've kept since Ambition Record. BTW, if know how to get the passive 'spin', please tell. Ha!

Good work kemco and EXE-CREATE, this is indeed another fine gem for the kemco rpg collection, I was at first worried for this one, but Im glad the whole thing goes pretty well together to keep the interest going and some good humour to boot, but not too silly. just a nice all round fun game peppered with some fun quirks..
Another great Kemco game, they just get better and better. With the storyline, the quirky characters and improvements in controls this is my favorite so far.

Once again a Kemco triumph, everything that makes their games great delivered with improvements. Good story, nice graphics, great gameplay, excellent development, and the opportunity to obtain all the in app purchases through level building. Personal opinion of course, but for me Kemco are the developers to beat
